OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782370082
OL,3,CFrance confirms first Ebola case in
OL,4,Cdoctor returning from DR Congo
OL,6,FFrench health authorities have
OL,7,Fconfirmed the country's first known
OL,8,Fcase of Ebola, identified in a doctor
OL,9,Freturning to France from the
OL,10,FDemocratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
OL,12,FIn a statement released on Wednesday,
OL,13,FFrance's health ministry said the
OL,14,Fhumanitarian medic is now in a "stable
OL,15,Fcondition", having been immediately
OL,16,Ftaken to a specialised facility.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782370082
OL,3,CFrance confirms first Ebola case in
OL,4,Cdoctor returning from DR Congo
OL,6,FFrance has "specialised capabilities
OL,7,Ffor managing highly transmissible
OL,8,Finfectious diseases", the ministry
OL,9,Fsaid, with patients treated in "a
OL,10,Fdesignated healthcare facility,
OL,11,Ffollowing strict biosafety protocols".
OL,13,F"All precautionary measures, including
OL,14,Fthe patient's isolation, were taken
OL,15,Fupon his arrival in the country, with
OL,16,Ftransfer to the hospital under secure
OL,17,Fconditions to prevent any risk of
OL,18,Fcontamination," the statement said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782370082
OL,3,CFrance confirms first Ebola case in
OL,4,Cdoctor returning from DR Congo
OL,6,F"A thorough epidemiological
OL,7,Finvestigation is underway to identify
OL,8,Findividuals who may have been in
OL,9,Fcontact with the patient.
OL,11,F"These individuals will be contacted
OL,12,Fwithout delay by the regional health
OL,13,Fagency, will undergo 21 days of home
OL,14,Fisolation, and will be closely
OL,15,Fmonitored during this period."
OL,17,FIt comes after the World Health
OL,18,FOrganisation (WHO) declared a "Public
OL,19,FHealth Emergency of International
OL,20,FConcern" on May 17 in response to the
OL,21,Fspread of the Ebola virus in the DRC.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
